<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,763,932]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName authority="Bloch, 1787" authorityName="Bloch" authorityYear="1787" box="[151,583,799,824]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Scophthalmidae" genus="Zeugopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleuronectiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctatus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,583,799,824]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,417,800,823]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Zeugopterus punctatus</emphasis>
(Bloch, 
<number box="[518,575,799,824]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1787.0">1787</number>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was doubtfully reported for the Mediterranean coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[1228,1292,799,823]" name="Spain" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Spain</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="De Buen, F. (1935) Fauna ictiologica. Catalogo de los peces ibericos: de la planicie continental, aguas dulces, pelagicas y de los abismos proximos. Primera parte. Notas y Resumenes Instituto Espanol Oceanografia, 2 (88), 1 - 89." type="journal article">
<collectingCountry box="[1336,1369,800,823]" name="South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">De</collectingCountry>
Buen (
<number box="[159,220,836,860]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1935.0">1935</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. This record is erroneous according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Tortonese" box="[665,857,836,860]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Tortonese, E. (1975) Osteichthyes (Pesci ossei). Parte seconda. Fauna d'Italia. Vol. 11. Edizioni Calderini, Bologna, 636 pp." type="book" year="1975">
Tortonese (
<number box="[790,848,836,860]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1975.0">1975</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and considered doubtful by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nielsen" box="[1177,1347,836,860]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Nielsen, J. G. (1979) Scophthalmidae. In: Hureau, J. C. &amp; Monod, T. (Eds.), Check-list of the fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and of the Mediterranean (Clofnam). Vol. 1. Unesco, Paris, pp. 616 - 619." type="book" year="1979">
Nielsen (
<number box="[1278,1339,836,860]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1979.0">1979</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. An old specimen from Valencia (
<collectingCountry box="[454,521,871,895]" name="Spain" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Spain</collectingCountry>
) held in the Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, Madrid was studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Matallanas" box="[151,357,908,932]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Matallanas, J. (1984) Consideraciones sobre algunos pleuronectiformes (Pisces, Teleostei) nuevos o de dudosa presencia en las costas orientales ibericas. Miscellania Zoologica, 8, 197 - 202." type="journal article" year="1984">
Matallanas (
<number box="[289,349,908,932]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" value="1984.0">1984</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, but this specimen is not provided with precise data of capture.
